tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE security_breach_attempts (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50),
    attempted_action VARCHAR(100),
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE security_logs (
    log_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    event_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    event_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    user_id INT NOT NULL,
    message TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE breach_attempts (
    attempt_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    event_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    user_id INT NOT NULL,
    ip_address VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    attempt_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE security_logs (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    event_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    event_details TEXT,
    user_id INT);

CREATE TABLE breach_attempts (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    user_id INT,
    ip_address VARCHAR(15) NOT NULL,
    message TEXT);

CREATE TABLE triggers (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    trigger_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    trigger_action VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL);

CREATE TABLE alert_notifications (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    alert_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    message TEXT,
    notification_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    is_read BOOLEAN);

CREATE TABLE admin_users (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    role VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL);
